[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [1mscp [22mcopies files between hosts on a network.[m
[m
       [1mscp [22muses the SFTP protocol over a [4mssh[24m(1) connection for data transfer, and uses the same authentication and provides the same  se‐[m
       curity as a login session.[m
[m
       [1mscp [22mwill ask for passwords or passphrases if they are needed for authentication.[m
[m
       The  [4msource[24m and [4mtarget[24m may be specified as a local pathname, a remote host with optional path in the form [user@]host:[path], or a[m
       URI in the form scp://[user@]host[:port][/path].  Local file names can be made explicit using absolute or  relative  pathnames  to[m
       avoid [1mscp [22mtreating file names containing ‘:’ as host specifiers.[m
[m
